main event: A bright yellow ball of fire resembling a falling star was observed in Tampa, Florida in 1958. It traveled north, then east, orbited, and eventually disappeared.
interesting points: The object was seen traveling in different directions before disappearing, indicating an unconventional flight path.
The source of the observation was a civilian.
The report indicates a probability of an aircraft due to the description, duration, and flight path.
The conclusion was that there was insufficient data for evaluation, leaving the object as 'Unknown'.
